<section xml:id="sec-real-numbers" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Real Numbers</title>
    <p>
        Real numbers are set of numbers that include all rational and irrational numbers. They can be represented on the number line and include:
    </p>
    <tabular left="medium" top="medium">
        <row >
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Category</cell>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Example</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium" >Whole numbers</cell>
            <cell bottom="medium" right="medium">All numbers including <m>0</m> such as <m>0, 1, 2</m> </cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Integers</cell>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Incudes: <m>-4,-3,-2,0,1,2</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Fractions</cell>
            <cell bottom="medium" right="medium"><m>\frac{1}{2}, \frac{2}{3}, \frac{1}{3},\frac{5}{4},\frac{12}{6}</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Decimals</cell>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium"><m>0.2,4.5,-2.6</m></cell>

        </row>
        <row>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium">Irrational numbers</cell>
            <cell right="medium" bottom="medium"><m>\sqrt{2}, \pi</m> </cell>
        </row>
    </tabular>
   
    <p>
        Real numbers include all numbers we use in daily life, they can be positive, negative, or zero. 
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{NOTE:}</m> Real numbers do not include imaginary numbers like the square root of <m>-1</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
        <m>{\color{blue}\text{Why do we study real numbers?}}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        We use real numbers to manage money while budgeting or shopping for items, to measure ingredients when cooking, to track time and distance while traveling, and to understand data on digital devices. 
    </p>
